title: For Sale:  1916 Spanish 7mm Mauser w/bayonet
postcontent: (See important NOTE at the bottom)Have available for sale is a 1916 model Spanish Mauser Short Rifle.  These Mausers came out of the Fabrica de Armas de Oviedo plant, otherwise known as the Oviedo Arsenal.  These rifles were used in the Spanish Civil War which was from 1936 to 1939.  This rifle likely saw duty in the Civil War and has plenty of markings showing the use over many years.  I purchased it in "good" condition, added it to my Mauser collection, and never fired it.  With the rifle I purchased a box of 7mm ammo made for the Venezuelan army by FN in Belgium.  I am also including a box of PPU, 20 rounds.    I was also able to pick up a Mauser bayonet with scabbard that fits the rifle, but is not likely to be of Spanish origin.  I am also including some leather ammo pouches that were probably made later, but like the rifle, will need some cleaning up.NOTE:  Due to excessive spam received in replies to the ads, primarily people phishing for email addresses, I will not reply to a response if you don't provide a phone number, or if I am unable to Google your email address and confirm it is valid.

title: For Sale:  Zastava Yugo M48 8mm Mauser Package
postcontent: Up for sale is a new or like new Zastava M48 carbine.  This is the first version that is all milled before they started adding cheaper, stamped components.  These were made right after WWII and were almost the same as the K98K.  The Zastava factory was taken over by the Nazis in 1941 through 1944.  After the Nazis were conquered, the factory went back to Yugoslavian control and many of the original workers returned.  I also suspect actual K98K carbines were made at Zastava.  Since Yugoslavia didn't have any major wars, these were mothballed, some never shot.  This was purchased right out of the crate full of cosmolene which was cleaned off.  This particular rifle was likely made in 1950 and stored ever since.  As you can see in the picture, it has a full logo on the receiver and indicates it is the M48 (original) version.I am including an actual German K98K sling which is well worn, but is the same style as was used on this carbine.  Also including some ammo pouches in good condition and five boxes of 8mm ammo.This is one of four Mausers up for sale including a 1916 Spanish, 1938 Turkish, and a German K98K.

I have a Stevens 520 12ga takedown shotgun with an 18" barrel branded by Sears as a Ranger Repeater Shotgun model 30. Recently totally cleaned and ready to go to work. Yes, this will slam fire, hold the trigger and pump til the mag is empty. And it breaks in half for compact storage. A very interesting gun. It is the double humpback with sliding "suicide safety."
